      <div type="commentary" xml:lang="eng">
	<p>This edition is based on Andrew Ollett’s reading of the inscription <hi rend="italic">in situ</hi> in February 2017 and photographs taken at that time.</p>
	<p>The word <foreign xml:lang="pra-Latn">hālika</foreign> is probably a proper name; <bibl><ptr target="bibl:CTI"/></bibl> and <bibl><ptr target="bibl:ASWI4"/></bibl> interpreted it as “ploughman.”</p>
      </div>
      <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
	<ab>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	  <persName key="pers:Bha-Bādhā">bādhaya</persName> <persName key="pers:Bha-Hālika">hālika</persName>jayāya dānaṃ
	</ab>
      </div>
      <div type="apparatus" xml:lang="eng">
	<listApp>
	  <app loc="1">
	    <lem>bādhaya</lem>
	    <rdg source="#CTI">bodhiyā</rdg>
	    <note resp="staff:Ollett">I do not see a long-vowel mark after the <hi rend="italic">ya</hi>, although the inscription is quite worn.</note>
	  </app>
	</listApp>
      </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng">
	<ab>
	  The gift of 
	  <persName key="pers:Bha-Bādhā">Bādhā</persName>, the 
	  wife of <persName key="pers:Bha-Hālika">Hālika</persName>.
	</ab>
